<section class="landing-overview">
  <h2>// About PaperMaker //</h2>
  <p class="overview-content">
    PaperMaker was built with the scientific and research communities in mind. We understand the complexities of setting up local LaTeX compilers, tracking package versions, and managing style files while trying to write a journal submission or a technical report. PaperMaker provides an instantly available, zero-setup, secure editing and compilation workspace on the cloud, so you can focus entirely on your content and mathematics.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="landing-faq">
  <h2>// Frequently Asked Questions //</h2>
  <div class="faq-grid">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is PaperMaker free to use?</h3>
      <p>Yes, PaperMaker is completely free for researchers, scientists, and students globally. There are no premium lockouts or compilation limits.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Do I need to install packages locally?</h3>
      <p>No installation is required. Everything runs in isolated cloud compilation environments loaded with standard scientific packages.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Are my draft reports secure?</h3>
      <p>Your privacy is our priority. Each compilation job runs in a fully isolated containerized workspace that is securely removed afterwards.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

